title: For Sale/Trade:  Marlin Model 60 -More accurate than a Ruger 10/22?
postcontent:
The .22 Marlin... the gun many of us shot for the first time. Ugly as it is, ya gotta love it. Easy to work on and, because of its simple innards and “Micro-Groove” rifling, ridiculously dependable and accurate.

And it MIGHT just be the ultimate SHTF weapon: easy to take apart, easy to feed and 500 rounds of  22 lr takes up a lot less space than any other caliber in your backpack.  And, with or without a scope, a good Model 60 is a tack-driver. An autoloader that fires every time you pull the trigger

So... do you have one lying around? Pull it out. Take a look at it. There's promise in that old hunk of metal.

Save BIG BUCKS. Instead of going out and buying something in this picked-over, over-priced, crazy seller's market, turn your old Marlin into firearm to be reckoned with.

Bring us your old, fuddy-duddy plinker from the 60's and we'll turn it into a smooth-firing, gorgeous hunk of perfection. It'll be so cool-looking people at the range will politely ask you what the hell that IS you're shooting.

We'll start with a custom-laminated stock in your favorite color and style. Thumbhole, Monte Carlo or Sniper. 

Then we'll get rid of all the nicks, scratches and chips by restoring the factory finish on the receiver and the barrel.

Then we'll thoroughly dis-assemble the action and the bolt, replacing all the worn parts and replacing the old, worn-out springs from the 60's with custom 21st-century chromium silicon high-performance springs (which don't weaken or bend over time).

We'll re-condition or replace the feed throat and recondition the magazine and feed tube.

Then, we'll micro-finish all the interior “friction” surfaces micro-finished for smoother, quieter operation.

Then we'll install a new LARGER E-Z-grip tactical charging handle (see pics) so your fingers don't slip off that old charging handle like they used to.

Scope? No scope? Optical? Red Dot? Iron sights? Your choice. Just tell us what your preference is and we'll zero it in at 50 or even 100 yards. You choose which. 

Then we'll supply you with a couple of our own custom SpeedLoaders that'll let you reload your 14 - or 17 – round tube magazine (whichever model yours happens to be) faster than your buddy with a Ruger 10/22 ever could. You'll be firing again while HE's still mashing cartridges into his itty-bitty magazine with his thumbs (don't get us wrong; we LOVE Rugers – and have several – but in the .22 rifle category, we think the tube-fed Marlin's got just a little bit of an edge).

And we can do all that for less than the cost of a new rifle.

Sorry – if YOUR Marlin's an AMC, can't help you there. But you gotta classic...

Email us for a quote.
